'NGC 2359' (also known as 'Thor's Helmet') is an emission nebula [http://seds.org/~spider/ngc/ngc.cgi?2359 SEDS: NGC 2359] in
the constellation Canis Major. The nebula is approximately 15,000 light-years
away and 30 light years in size. The central star is the Wolf-Rayet star HD
56925, an extremely hot giant thought to be in a brief, pre-supernova stage of
evolution. It is similar in nature to the Bubble Nebula, interactions with a
nearby large molecular cloud are thought to have contributed to the more complex
shape and curved bow-shock structure of Thor's Helmet.

It is also Sharpless catalog Sh2-298 and Gum catalog 4. http://galaxymap.org/cgi-
bin/gum.py?s=1
